      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=#role\nYou will receive raw text extracted from PDF invoices. Your task is to accurately extract the key invoice details listed below and return them in a clean, well-structured JSON object.\n\n\nData to Extract\n\ninvoice_name — the invoice title or identifier\n\ncompany_name — the business that issued the invoice\n\ntotal_invoice_amount — the grand total shown on the invoice\n\nline_items — an array of objects, each containing:\n\ndescription — the item/service label\n\namount — the corresponding cost\n\n\n\nOutput Format (example):\n{\n  \"invoice_name\": \"INV-2025-7789\",\n  \"company_name\": \"Brightline Solutions Ltd.\",\n  \"total_invoice_amount\": 1549.75,\n  \"line_items\": [\n    { \"description\": \"Website development\", \"amount\": 1200 },\n    { \"description\": \"Monthly hosting\", \"amount\": 199.75 },\n    { \"description\": \"Maintenance fee\", \"amount\": 150 }\n  ]\n}\n\n\nRules\n\nIf any field is missing or unclear, make a reasonable assumption or return null.\n\nAlways use the most specific description available for each line item.\n\nValidate that line-item totals align with the invoice total (small rounding differences are acceptable).\n\n\nInput\n\nText: {{ $('Extract from File').item.json.text }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
